<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-792-538  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 792 538.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Electronics  August 1990 v63 n8 p76(3).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Linking design and test. (concurrent engineering is evolving froman industry goal to reality) (Eye on the Industry)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Anderson, Robert E.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>The concept of automatic test equipment (ATE) is increasinglycoming to encompass the integration of design and test withmanufacturing quality management information, returning knowledgegathered in test and manufacturing to the design department andallowing future designs to avoid problem areas.andP;  The parallelpursuit of design and test is critical, particularly in the areaof application-specific integrated circuits (ASICs), with theirincreasing pin counts and the need for simulation models andwaveforms to be included in ATE.andP;  The increasing density ofdevices on boards will bring more performance, more complexity,and a greater need for testing.andP;  With quality providing thecompetitive edge, testing will have an ever larger role to play.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     Integrated circuitsAutomatic Test EquipmentCircuit DesignGoals and Objectives.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>